20
00:00:48,780 --> 00:00:49,780
Oh, no.

21
00:00:50,440 --> 00:00:50,740
Fine.

22
00:00:50,740 --> 00:00:51,180
Fine.

23
00:00:51,320 --> 00:00:53,320
It is the ultimate digital trap.

24
00:00:53,660 --> 00:00:54,840
I mean, it really is.

25
00:00:54,880 --> 00:00:55,860
It's terrifying.

26
00:00:55,860 --> 00:01:02,180
You're suddenly holding this tiny, glowing rectangle, staring at four letters, and your

27
00:01:02,180 --> 00:01:05,080
brain is just shifting into absolute overdrive.

28
00:01:05,140 --> 00:01:06,360
And it has to, right.

29
00:01:06,440 --> 00:01:09,900
Because you have absolutely zero acoustic context.

30
00:01:10,100 --> 00:01:10,760
None at all.

31
00:01:10,800 --> 00:01:13,060
Is that an angry, jaw-clenched fine?

32
00:01:13,640 --> 00:01:13,840
Right.

33
00:01:13,920 --> 00:01:16,500
Like, I am furious, but I am agreeing.

34
00:01:16,780 --> 00:01:17,260
Exactly.

35
00:01:17,640 --> 00:01:21,440
Or is it a happy, easygoing, sure, whatever you want, that's fine.

36
00:01:21,440 --> 00:01:26,780
Or maybe it's just an exhausted fine, like, I just worked a 12-hour shift, and I cannot

37
00:01:26,780 --> 00:01:28,340
